track_notes: Sycamore Canyon is beautiful, and worth hiking on its own merit -- up to a point. There is a very challenging slot canyon at N31.41424 W111.19606, and the only way I could get through was by using a helper rope on a steep slope, immediately above a deep pool of water. If you do make it past this point, continue to the end of my track and recommend exiting the wash at N31.39338 W111.20451. I am going to try to approach the summit from Summit Mountain Highway, then Sycamore Canyon hike. This should approach the summit from the SE direction.
